{
  "doc_id": "3918",
  "text": "The perturbation to the deep-ocean environment at the P/E boundary led to a major extinction event among benthic foraminifers (35-50% of species; see [CITATION_1] . Deep-ocean ostracodes also show a perturbation shifting to an assemblage of smaller size and thinner walls (consistent with benthic foraminiferal changes), although there is no associated extinction [CITATION_2] . The dominant factors that have been considered as causing the extinction are decreased oxygenation and increased corrosiveness of deep and intermediate waters, and changes in surface water productivity affecting deepocean nutrient availability [CITATION_3] .",
